title: fernet_con_coca
body:
Fernet con coca (meaning "Fernet with Coke" in Spanish) is a long drink of Argentine origin consisting of the Italian amaro liqueur fernet and cola, served over ice. Although typically made with Fernet-Branca and Coca-Cola.
It is now considered a cultural icon of [[Argentina]] and is especially associated with its home province of Córdoba, where the drink is most consumed. The popularity of fernet con coca is such that Argentina consumes more than 75% of all fernet produced globally.
Walkers commonly make a "viajero" (meaning "traveller" in Spanish), using half-cut plastic bottles of Coca-Cola as containers for communal drinking and to carry the cocktail.

title: nsv
body:
The NSV is a 12.7 mm [b][[heavy machine gun]][/b] of [[Soviet]] origin. The weapon took its name from the three designers, G. I. [b]Nikitin[/b] (Г. И. Никитин), Y. S. [b]Sokolov[/b] (Ю. М. Соколов) and V. I. [b]Volkov[/b] (В. И. Волков). It was designed to replace the [[DShK]]  and it was adopted by the [[Soviet Army]] in 1971.

The NSV weighs 25 kg, has a rate of fire of 700–800 rounds per minute, and an effective range from 1,500 m to 2,000 m against airborne and ground targets, respectively. A loaded ammunition belt with 50 rounds weighs 11 kg. It is commonly mounted on [[military vehicles]] like [[T-64]], [[T-72]], or [[T-80]] [[tank]]s. 

It is no longer being produced in [[Russia]]; the manufacturing license for the NSV ended up in Kazakhstan after the break-up of the Soviet Union. The NSV has been manufactured in Bulgaria, India, Poland and Yugoslavia under license. The new [[kord 6p50|Kord machine gun]] has replaced worn-out NSVs since 1998.

title: krag_jorgensen
body:
A [b]Norwegian [[bolt action|bolt-action]] [[rifle]][/b], designed in 1886. The weapon name took its name from the designers - Ole Herman Johannes Krag and Erik Jørgensen. It was adopted as a standard rifle by [[Norway]], [[Denmark]], and the [[United States]]. 

A distinctive feature of the Krag–Jørgensen action is its [[magazine (weapon)|magazine]]. While many other rifles of its era use an integral box magazine loaded by a charger or stripper clip, the magazine of the Krag–Jørgensen is integral with the receiver. It features an opening on the right hand side with a hinged cover. Instead of a charger, single cartridges are inserted through the side opening, and are pushed up, around, and into the action by a spring follower. Later, similar to a charger, a claw type clip would be made for the Krag that allowed the magazine to be loaded all at once, also known as the Krag "speedloader magazine". 

h4. See also

* Wikipedia article: "Krag-Jørgensen":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Krag%E2%80%93J%C3%B8rgensen]

title: kuzuda_yone
body:
Kuzuda Yone is an [[UTAU|UTAUloid]] designed by [[kuru2suuzi|Kurukuru Suuzi]]. [[kuru2suuzi|Suuzi]] also provided her voice for Yone's voicebank. Yone's voice is described as sweet, feminine, and somewhat childish. 

Her name Yone consists of the characters 夜 (Yo) and 音 (Ne), meaning "night" and "sound" respectively. Her surname Kuzuda consists of the characters 葛 (Kuzu), the kanji for "kudzu", also called Japanese arrowroot, and 駄 (Da), meaning "worthless" or "low-grade". Spoken aloud, her full name 葛駄夜音 (Kuzuda Yone) sounds like the phrase クズだよね (Kuzu da yo ne), meaning "Trash, isn't it?".

Yone is an [[oni]] who has lived for 312 years, but appears to be 12 years old. The [[hand mouth|mouth on her hand]] has no tongue so she cannot taste with it, but she can use it to store items in her body. She enjoys mischief and acting like a brat. She has [[very long hair|very long]] [[white hair|white]] or [[grey hair|grey]] hair and often wears a [[striped kimono]]. Her eyes (or [[one-eyed|eye]]?) are [[covered eyes|covered]] by a sheet with a single [[green eyes|eye]] on it.

(Character details sourced from the "UTAU wiki":[http://utau.wikidot.com/utau:yone-kuzuda] and [[kuru2suuzi|Suuzi's]] "official site":[https://kurukuru2suuzi.wixsite.com/kuzutokaze/%E8%A4%87%E8%A3%BD-%E8%91%9B%E9%A7%84-%E5%A4%9C%E9%9F%B3])

title: 9a-91
body:
9A-91 is a [b]Russian compact [[assault rifle]][/b] that fires subsonic 9×39mm [[ammunition|cartridge]]. It was introduced in 1993 as a cheaper versatile alternative to [[SR-3MP|SR-3 Vikhr]]. The weapon features a stamped steel receiver, polymer furniture, top-[[folding stock]], a sight mounting rail for [[optical sight|optics]] on the receiver's left side, and a quick detach [[suppressor]]. Due to its cartridge's lower muzzle velocity, the effective firing range is lower than most assault rifles, 200 m.

[b]Avatar[/b] is a film franchise written, designed, and directed by [[James Cameron]]. Spawning out of the 2009 film [[Avatar (2009 film)|]], the franchise's title refers to the genetically engineered Na'vi clones that serve as avatars to the minds of remotely located humans, and are used to interact with the natives and environment of Pandora in the first movie. The franchise follows the [[Na'vi]], a humanoid alien species indigenous to Pandora, and [[Jake Sully]], who is the titular Avatar.

title: songkran
body:
A [[festival]] held in several Indochinese countries, typically between 13 - 15 April. Though the most notable and popular being the one held in [[Thailand]]. Also known as "water festival".

Originally, the festival coincides with the traditional new year of the region (14 April) and mostly involves modest water sprinkling as a form of blessing. In modern times, however, it has transformed into a water festival where partipants shower each other with [[water]], often with a [[water gun]].

h4. See also

* [[Water gun]]

title: numa_numa_(meme)

Both in English and in Japanese, the lyrics were misheard as a mondegreen in those languages. The "lyrics" in Japanese can be found "here":[https://utaten.com/lyric/kz15032119/].
The chorus is misheard as "Drink, drink, yay!", so in Japanese will often be seen accompanied with people drinking alcohol.

Post #42977 was a popular flash animation of the Japanese version of the meme, illustrating the Japanese interpretation of the lyrics.

Many of its design features are directly intended to address the weaknesses of the M16S1 as encountered operationally by some infantrymen. The rifle is being sold for export use aside from domestic use. In the United States, it was marketed by ST Kinetics via its American subsidiary, VT Systems.

title: browning_auto_5
body:
[b]The Browning Automatic-5[/b] or simply Auto-5 or A-5 is a recoil-operated [b]semi-automatic [[shotgun]][/b] designed by John Browning. It was the first successful semi-automatic shotgun design, and remained in production until 1998.

It was the first mass-produced semi-automatic shotgun. Designed in 1898 and patented in 1900, it was produced continually for almost 100 years by several makers with production ending in 1998. It features a distinctive high rear end, earning it the nickname "Humpback". The top of the action goes straight back on a level with the barrel before cutting down sharply towards the buttstock. This distinctive feature makes it easy to identify A-5s from a distance. A-5s were produced in a variety of gauges, with 12 and 20 predominating; 16 gauge (not produced between 1976 and 1987) models were also available. The shotgun saw [[military]] service worldwide from [[World War I]] through the [[Vietnam War.]] The weapon was used heavily by members of the [[Special Air Service]] in the Malayan Emergency, who found the semi-automatic shotgun perfect for close quarter jungle fighting.

title: lyon_(city)
body:
Lyon is the third-largest city and second-largest metropolitan area of [[France]]. It is located at the confluence of the rivers Rhône and Saône, 391 km southeast of [[Paris]], 278 km north of [[Marseille]], 113 km southwest of Geneva, and 50 km northeast of Saint-Étienne.

The city of Lyon proper had a population of 522,969 in 2019 within its small municipal territory of 48 km2, but together with its suburbs and exurbs the Lyon metropolitan area had a population of 2,280,845 that same year, the second most populated in France. Lyon and 58 suburban municipalities have formed since 2015 the Metropolis of Lyon, a directly elected metropolitan authority now in charge of most urban issues, with a population of 1,411,571 in 2019. Lyon is the prefecture of the Auvergne-Rhône-Alpes region and seat of the Departmental Council of Rhône (whose jurisdiction, however, no longer extends over the Metropolis of Lyon since 2015).

The capital of the Gauls during the Roman Empire, Lyon is the seat of an archbishopric whose holder bears the title of Primate of the Gauls. Lyon became a major economic hub during the Renaissance. The city is recognised for its cuisine and gastronomy, as well as historical and architectural landmarks; as such, the districts of Old Lyon, the Fourvière hill, the Presqu'île and the slopes of the Croix-Rousse are inscribed on the UNESCO World Heritage List. Lyon was historically an important area for the production and weaving of silk. Lyon played a significant role in the history of cinema since Auguste and Louis Lumière invented the cinematograph there. The city is also known for its light festival, the Fête des Lumières, which begins every 8 December and lasts for four days, earning Lyon the title of "Capital of Lights".

A utility pole is a column or post, frequently made of wood, used to support overhead [[power lines]] and various other public utilities, such as electrical cable, fiber optic cable, and related equipment such as [[transformer|transformers]] and street lights. 

Depending on the application they may be referred by various names, such as transmission pole, telephone pole, telecommunication pole, power pole, telegraph pole, and telegraph post.

title: cable_tie
body:
A cable tie (also known as a zip tie) is a type of fastener for holding items together, particularly electrical cables and wires.  Most cable tie consists of a flexible nylon tape with an integrated gear rack on one end and a small opening with a ratchet on the other.  The gear rack is inserted into the opening and past the ratchet which prevents it from being able to be pulled back out.

Cable ties are sometimes used as a [[restrained|restraint]], since they can usually only be pulled tighter once they're tightened.  Usually used tying the wrists or thumbs together.

body:
A bow is a [[weapon]] that shoots [[arrow (projectile)|]]s. The weapon is used for hunting, sport shooting, and occasionally for war.

Regular bows (covered by this tag) are pulled back manually, which takes more strength than popular belief would tend to attribute to the typical archer character in fiction. However, in later times, a version of the weapon called a [[crossbow]] would arise, which replaces manual pulling of the string with pulling by means of a mechanical device such as a lever or a crank, which allows for more powerful shots and can be used by those with less strength than a regular archer.

title: chaise_longue
body:
A chaise longue (French for "long chair") is an upholstered [[couch|sofa]] in the shape of a chair that is long enough to support the legs.

It is also known as a "chaise lounge" (Primarily North American) due to a misspelling of the name during its introduction in North America.  Given the purpose of the chair was to lounge around on, the misspelled naming has stuck.

The outdoor furniture called [[lounge_chair|sun loungers/lounge chairs]] are also referred to as "chaise lounges" in North America, likely due to the similar shape.

The French now use the term "chaise longue" to refer to any kind of long reclining chair, such as deck chairs and sun loungers, but for tagging purposes this tag is only for the indoor furniture.

title: trading_card
body:
A [b]trading card[/b], also known as [b]collectible card[/b], are [[card]]s that are traditionally included in products such as [[cigarette]]s, [[food]], and [[candy]]. Originally depicting sportpersons, automobiles, and scenery. Though in later era, trading cards usually depict characters from fictional works, typically from movie or television series.

Since the creation of [[Magic: The Gathering]] in 1993, a derivative of trading card known as trading [[card game]] has emerged, which involves using these cards as a game piece. These has since supplanted the traditional trading card market, albeit the non-game trading cards (such as [[soccer|footballer]] cards) were still being produced to this day.

This tag is applicable to the depiction of either trading cards or the trading card games, including the real and fan-made card face. If the cards were shown to be played, the tag [[card game]] is applicable.

title: 1pn58
body:
A [[Soviet]] designed passive [b][[night vision|night]] [[scope]][/b] for a range of Soviet designed [[gun|small arms]] and [[grenade launcher]]s. The name comes from the GRAU index. 1PN is the GRAU index of night vision devices, where PN stands for [i]Nochnoy Pritsel[/i] (Russian: Ночной прицел) meaning night sight. It is also called NSPUM (НСПУМ) or NSPU-1. The scope was introduced into Soviet [[military]] service in the early 1970s and is still used by many of the Soviet Union's successor states, and has been used in numerous armed conflicts around the world.

The 1PN58 gathers light into a refractor which can be protected with an aperture cover. The center of the cover has a circular aperture with dark glass allowing the scope to be used in light conditions that would otherwise saturate the light intensifier. For zeroing the sight the left side of the scope has two perpendicular knobs, of which the elevation knob has a detachable scale. The scope comes with seven different, detachable elevation scales, one for each of the supported weapons. Its magnification power is 3.5×.

Any [[weapon]] fitted with the Soviet-style dovetail mount can technically use this optic. The following weapons can use the 1PN58, such as:
* [[AKM]]
* [[AK-74]]
* AK-100 series 
* [[AS Val]]
* [[Dragunov SVD]] and SVDK
* [[PKM]]
* [[PSL Romak]]
* [[RPG-7]]
* [[RPK-74]] and RPK-74M
* [[VSS Vintorez]]
* [[Zastava M76]]

title: twister_(submission_hold)
body:
A sideways body bend and neck crank-type [[submission hold]] in [[mixed martial arts]], which involves forcing the head towards the shoulder while controlling the body, hence causing lateral hyperflexion of the cervical spine. 

The technique involves tension in several body parts, and depending on the flexibility of the recipient, can also involve pain in the knees, abdominals and torso. The twister is often confused as being a spine crank since it involves a degree of lateral non-cervical spinal flexion. The main pressure is however on the cervical spine, hence making it a neck crank. It is performed from a back mount single vine ride position, where the top man has one "hook" threaded through the bottom man's legs and secured behind the ankle. The top man then pulls the bottom man's opposite arm behind his own head and grabs hold of his opponent's head, pulling it down to his shoulder. 

It resembles a hold in professional [[wrestling]] called the [I][[Cobra Twist]][/I] (actually, the latter is basically its standing counterpart) though the Twister itself is used in pro wrestling as well, being popularized by former [[Ultimate Fighting Championship|UFC]] fighter and current [[WWE]] wrestler Matt Riddle, calling his version of the hold as the [I]Bromission[/I].

title: osmanthus_fragrans
body:
[b]Osmanthus fragrans[/b], commonly known as sweet osmanthus, sweet olive, tea olive, fragrant olive, and in Japanese as [i]mokusei[/i], is a species of the [[Osmanthus]] genus of plants native to southeast Asia.

It is an evergreen shrub or small tree, with clusters of small (1 cm), four-lobed flowers ranging in color from white through pale yellow to orange-yellow. In Japan, subspecies with white and orange flowers are distinguished, called "[[silver osmanthus]]" (銀木犀, [i]ginmokusei[/i]) and "[[gold osmanthus]]" (金木犀, [i]kinmokusei[/i]) respectively.

It is widely cultivated, both in and out of its native range, for its strong fragrance. Its flowers are used in jams, desserts, and as an infusion for tea.

title: h&k_xm8
body:
A lightweight [[assault rifle]] system developed from the late 1990s to early 2000s. The [[rifle]] was designed by German small arms manufacturer Heckler & Koch, and shares design and engineering with their [[h&k g36|G36]] rifle.
The XM8 is a selective-fire 5.56×45mm NATO assault rifle, firing from a closed rotary bolt. Its design and functioning is similar to that of the G36, of which it is a derivative.

The materials used to build the XM8 are almost entirely composites, with the notable exception of the cold-hammer-forged steel barrel. Preliminary tests in [[desert]] and arctic conditions have shown the XM8 to be a rugged weapon, though some complaints arose.

While the XM8 fell out of favor with the US military, Heckler & Koch sought to market the rifle globally. In the meantime, the Malaysian Armed Forces expressed interest in using the rifle and by 2007 openly stated its intention to purchase the XM8 rifle. By 2010, the Royal Malaysian Navy special unit PASKAL began using the XM8 along with other Heckler & Koch assault rifles including the [[h&k hk416|HK416]] and G36.

"Wikipedia page":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Heckler_%26_Koch_XM8]

title: 2022_fifa_world_cup
body:
The 2022 FIFA World Cup was the 22nd FIFA [[World Cup]], a tournament for the men's [[soccer]] world championship, taking place in [[Qatar]] from 20 November to 18 December 2022. It was the first World Cup to take place in the Middle East, the first to be held in autumn in the northern hemisphere, and the first to not be held in either May, June, or July, known to be extremely hot months in Qatar.

[[Argentina]] won their third World Cup against [[France]] in a 4-2 penalty shootout, after a 3-3 draw in extra time.

Even before the tournament began, it became the focal point of numerous controversies, primarily revolving around allegations of bribery of FIFA officials for the rights to host the tournament, poor treatment of workers (mostly immigrants), and suppression of LGBT rights.

title: f-104_starfighter
body:
The [i]Lockheed[/i] [b]F-104 Starfighter[/b] is a single-engine, supersonic interceptor aircraft originally developed by Lockheed for the United States Air Force (USAF). One of the Century Series of aircraft, it was operated by the air forces of more than a dozen nations (including the [[Japan Air Self-Defense Force]]) from 1958 to 2004.

The F-104 served with the USAF from 1958 until 1969, and continued with Air National Guard units until 1975. The National Aeronautics and Space Administration (NASA) flew a small mixed fleet of F-104 types in supersonic flight tests and spaceflight programs until 1994.

USAF F-104Cs saw service during the [[Vietnam War]], and F-104A aircraft were deployed by Pakistan briefly during the Indo-Pakistani wars. Republic of China Air Force (Taiwan) F-104s also engaged the People's Liberation Army Air Force (China) over the disputed island of Quemoy. The operational service of the Starfighter ended with its retirement by the Italian Air Force in May 2004.

It is, in many ways, superior to its predecessor. It has improved and perfected Twin Drive System, seven melee weapons like its predecessors, the [[Gundam Exia]] and [[00 Raiser]] but improved versions of them: a  single GN Sword V which is the last and most powerful among the GN Swords and six GN Sword Bits which have the highest overall stats among [[bit (gundam)|bit]] and [[funnels (gundam)|fang]] weapons in [[Gundam 00]], a more powerful version of the Raiser Sword nicknamed by the fans as the "Quantum Sword" which has the length of the moon's diameter and is accessible while in [[Trans-Am]] Mode, the Quantum Teleportation System which enables the 00 Qan[T] to travel and reach extremely long distances in deep space and the Quantum System, which is the improved derivative of the Trans-Am Burst System.

This tag also covers the more powerful variant of the ELS Qan[T], a version of the original machine that has fused with the extra terrestrial [[els|ELS]] species. In [i][[SD Gundam G-Generation|SD Gundam G-Generation Cross Rays]][/i] and [I][[SD Gundam Battle Alliance]][/I], the ELS Qan[T] is equipped with a switchblade-like [[gunblade]] that is similar to Exia's GN Sword and 00's GN Sword III, its GN Sword Bits are now capable of ranged combat by firing beams, and it can use its wings as tentacle-like, stabbing weapons.

title: avatar_(2009_film)
body:
[b]Avatar[/b] is a 2009 [[science fiction]] film written and directed by [[James Cameron]], starring Sam Worthington as [[Jake Sully]] and Zoe Saldana as [[Neytiri]]. 

The film is set in the mid 22nd century, when humans are mining a precious mineral called unobtanium on Pandora, a lush habitable moon of a gas giant in the Alpha Centauri star system. The expansion of the mining colony threatens the continued existence of a local tribe of [[Na'vi]], a humanoid [[alien]] species indigenous to Pandora. 

The film's title refers to the genetically engineered Na'vi clones that serve as avatars to the minds of remotely located humans, and are used to interact with the natives and environment of Pandora.

Avatar was internationally released on December 2009 to critical acclaim and commercial success. The film broke several box office records during its release and became the highest-grossing film of all time in North America and worldwide, surpassing [[Titanic (movie)|]]. The film held this record for ten years until the worldwide release of [[Avengers: Endgame]].

Following the film's success, Cameron signed with 20th Century Fox to produce two sequels, making Avatar the first of a planned trilogy.

Not to be confused with [[Avatar Legends]].

body:
The Siamese fighting fish (Betta splendens), commonly known as the betta, is a freshwater fish native to Southeast Asia.

Although aquarium specimens are widely known for their brilliant colors and large, flowing fins, the natural coloration of B. splendens is generally green, brown and grey, while the fins are short; wild fish exhibit strong colors only when agitated. In captivity, Siamese fighting fish have been selectively bred to display a vibrant array of colors and tail types.
